/**
 * ============================================================================
 * WHAT IS AN ENTERPRISE APPLICATION?
 * ============================================================================
 * 
 * An Enterprise Application is a large-scale software system designed to 
 * support complex business processes and operations of an organization.
 * 
 * Key Characteristics:
 * 1. Handles critical business functions
 * 2. Supports multiple users simultaneously
 * 3. Integrates with other systems
 * 4. Manages large volumes of data
 * 5. Provides high availability and reliability
 * 6. Supports business growth and scalability
 * 
 * Examples: Banking Systems, Telecom Systems, ERP Systems, CRM Systems
 * 
 * ============================================================================
 * BANKING SERVICES OVERVIEW
 * ============================================================================
 * 
 * Core Banking Services:
 * ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
 * │                        BANKING SERVICES                         │
 * ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
 * │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐ │
 * │  │   SAVINGS        │  │   CURRENT       │  │   FIXED         │ │
 * │  │   ACCOUNT        │  │   ACCOUNT       │  │   DEPOSITS      │ │
 * │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘ │
 * │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐ │
 * │  │   LOANS          │  │   INSURANCE     │  │   INVESTMENTS   │ │
 * │  │   - Home         │  │   - Life        │  │   - Mutual      │ │
 * │  │   - Car          │  │   - Health      │  │     Funds       │ │
 * │  │   - Personal     │  │   - Property    │  │   - Stocks      │ │
 * │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘ │
 * │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐ │
 * │  │   DIGITAL        │  │   PAYMENT       │  │   CUSTOMER      │ │
 * │  │   BANKING        │  │   SERVICES      │  │   SERVICES      │ │
 * │  │   - Mobile       │  │   - NEFT/RTGS   │  │   - CRM         │ │
 * │  │   - Net Banking  │  │   - UPI         │  │   - Complaints  │ │
 * │  │   - SMS Banking  │  │   - Bill Pay    │  │   - Support     │ │
 * │  │   - Phone Banking│  │   - Cards       │  │                 │ │
 * │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘ │
 * └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
 * 
 * ============================================================================
 * SAVINGS ACCOUNT - DETAILED BREAKDOWN
 * ============================================================================
 * 
 * A Savings Account is a fundamental banking product with various aspects:
 * 
 * 1. Account Management:
 *    - Account Opening
 *    - Account Closure
 *    - Account Updates (personal info, address, etc.)
 *    - Account Status (active, dormant, frozen)
 *    - KYC Compliance
 *    - Nomination Management
 * 
 * 2. Transactions:
 *    - Deposits (cash, cheque, transfer)
 *    - Withdrawals (cash, cheque, ATM)
 *    - Fund Transfers (NEFT, RTGS, IMPS, UPI)
 *    - Balance Inquiry
 *    - Mini Statement
 *    - Full Statement
 * 
 * 3. Interest Management:
 *    - Interest Calculation (daily/monthly/quarterly)
 *    - Interest Rate Changes
 *    - Interest Credit
 *    - Tax Deduction (TDS on interest)
 * 
 * 4. Charges and Fees:
 *    - Monthly Average Balance (MAB) penalty
 *    - Transaction charges
 *    - Cheque return charges
 *    - SMS alert charges
 *    - Debit card annual fees
 * 
 * 5. Security Features:
 *    - Debit/Credit Card Management
 *    - PIN Generation/Reset
 *    - Transaction Limits
 *    - Two-Factor Authentication
 *    - Fraud Detection
 *    - Block/Unblock Account
 * 
 * 6. Regulatory Compliance:
 *    - RBI Guidelines
 *    - KYC Norms
 *    - FATCA Reporting
 *    - PAN/Aadhaar linking
 * 
 * 7. Customer Services:
 *    - Account Balance SMS/Email
 *    - Transaction Alerts
 *    - E-statements
 *    - ATM Services
 *    - Cheque Book Request
 *    - Stop Payment Request
 * 
 * ============================================================================
 * PART 2: MONOLITHIC SERVICES
 * ============================================================================
 */

/**
 * ============================================================================
 * WHAT IS A MONOLITHIC SERVICE?
 * ============================================================================
 * 
 * A Monolithic Service is a traditional approach where all components of an
 * application are built as a single, tightly coupled unit.
 * 
 * Characteristics:
 * 1. Single codebase
 * 2. Single deployment unit (EAR/WAR file)
 * 3. Shared database
 * 4. Single technology stack
 * 5. All components run in the same process
 * 
 * Real-World Example - Bank Monolith:
 * ```
 * BankApp.war (Deployed on Application Server)
 * │
 * ├── Account Service
 * │   ├── Create Account
 * │   ├── Update Account
 * │   ├── Get Balance
 * │   └── Close Account
 * │
 * ├── Loan Service
 * │   ├── Apply Loan
 * │   ├── Approve Loan
 * │   ├── Get Loan Details
 * │   └── Close Loan
 * │
 * ├── Insurance Service
 * │   ├── Buy Insurance
 * │   ├── Claim Insurance
 * │   └── Renew Insurance
 * │
 * ├── Payment Service
 * │   ├── Process Payment
 * │   ├── Refund Payment
 * │   └── Get Payment Status
 * │
 * ├── Shared Database (Single Database)
 * └── Shared Resources (Memory, Threads)
 * ```
 * 
 * ============================================================================
 * REAL-WORLD SCENARIO: MONOLITH FAILURE
 * ============================================================================
 * 
 * Problem Statement:
 * A bank launched a monolithic application with all services packaged together.
 * During festival season, there was a surge in "Get Balance" requests.
 * A memory leak in the balance service caused the entire application to fail.
 * 
 * Impact:
 * 1. Loan agents couldn't submit loan applications
 * 2. Insurance agents couldn't process closures
 * 3. Customers couldn't report stolen cards
 * 4. Customer service queue backed up 25+ minutes
 * 5. Server restart required, causing 2-3 hours downtime
 * 
 * Root Cause:
 * - Single point of failure
 * - Memory leak in one service affecting all services
 * - No isolation between services
 * - All services share the same JVM
 * 
 * ============================================================================
 * DRAWBACKS OF MONOLITHIC SERVICES
 * ============================================================================
 * 
 * 1. SINGLE POINT OF FAILURE
 *    - If one service fails, everything fails
 *    - Memory leak in one service affects all
 *    - No fault isolation
 * 
 * 2. SCALING CHALLENGES
 *    - Must scale the entire application
 *    - Can't scale individual services
 *    - Resource wastage
 * 
 * 3. TECHNOLOGY LOCK-IN
 *    - Must use same technology stack for everything
 *    - Can't try new technologies
 *    - Difficult to upgrade
 * 
 * 4. DEVELOPMENT BOTTLENECKS
 *    - Large teams work on same codebase
 *    - Merge conflicts
 *    - Slow build times
 * 
 * 5. DEPLOYMENT RISKS
 *    - Any change requires full deployment
 *    - Risk of breaking everything
 *    - Long deployment cycles
 * 
 * 6. PERFORMANCE ISSUES
 *    - Memory leaks affect all services
 *    - One service can hog resources
 *    - Cascading failures
 * 
 * ============================================================================
 * PART 3: MICROSERVICES ARCHITECTURE
 * ============================================================================
 */

/**
 * ============================================================================
 * WHAT ARE MICROSERVICES?
 * ============================================================================
 * 
 * Microservices is an architectural style that structures an application as
 * a collection of loosely coupled, independently deployable services.
 * 
 * Key Characteristics:
 * 1. Each service runs independently
 * 2. Each service has its own database
 * 3. Services communicate via APIs
 * 4. Polyglot architecture (different tech stacks)
 * 5. Independently deployable
 * 6. Organized around business capabilities
 * 
 * Microservices Architecture Diagram:
 * ```
 * ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
 * │                        API GATEWAY                             │
 * │                   (Single Entry Point)                         │
 * └────────┬──────────────┬──────────────┬───────────────────────┘
 *          │              │              │
 *          ▼              ▼              ▼
 * ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐
 * │   Account    │ │    Loan      │ │  Insurance   │
 * │   Service    │ │   Service    │ │   Service    │
 * │   Port:8081  │ │  Port:8082   │ │  Port:8083   │
 * │  ┌────────┐  │ │  ┌────────┐  │ │  ┌────────┐  │
 * │  │Account │  │ │  │  Loan  │  │ │  │Insurance│  │
 * │  │  DB    │  │ │  │   DB   │  │ │  │   DB   │  │
 * │  └────────┘  │ │  └────────┘  │ │  └────────┘  │
 * └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘
 *          │              │              │
 *          ▼              ▼              ▼
 * ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
 * │                    EUREKA DISCOVERY SERVER                      │
 * │                   (Service Registry)                           │
 * └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
 * ```
 * 
 * ============================================================================
 * ADVANTAGES OF MICROSERVICES
 * ============================================================================
 * 
 * 1. INDEPENDENT DEPLOYMENT
 *    - Deploy each service independently
 *    - No risk of breaking other services
 *    - Faster deployment cycles
 * 
 * 2. SCALABILITY
 *    - Scale only the services that need it
 *    - Better resource utilization
 *    - Horizontal scaling
 * 
 * 3. FAULT ISOLATION
 *    - Issues are isolated to specific services
 *    - Failures don't cascade
 *    - Better resilience
 * 
 * 4. TECHNOLOGY DIVERSITY
 *    - Use best technology for each service
 *    - Try new technologies easily
 *    - Gradual upgrades
 * 
 * 5. TEAM AUTONOMY
 *    - Teams can own specific services
 *    - Faster development
 *    - Better accountability
 * 
 * 6. EASIER DEBUGGING
 *    - Issues are isolated to specific services
 *    - Easier to identify the faulty service
 *    - Faster problem resolution
 * 
 * 7. CONTINUOUS DELIVERY
 *    - Easier to implement CI/CD
 *    - Faster release cycles
 *    - Reduced risk
 * 
 * ============================================================================
 * CHALLENGES OF MICROSERVICES
 * ============================================================================
 * 
 * 1. DISTRIBUTED SYSTEM COMPLEXITY
 *    - Network latency
 *    - Service discovery
 *    - Distributed transactions
 * 
 * 2. DATA MANAGEMENT
 *    - Data consistency
 *    - Distributed transactions
 *    - Data synchronization
 * 
 * 3. OPERATIONAL COMPLEXITY
 *    - Monitoring multiple services
 *    - Logging and tracing
 *    - Health checks
 * 
 * 4. DEVELOPMENT COMPLEXITY
 *    - Service communication
 *    - Testing integration
 *    - Version management
 * 
 * 5. SECURITY
 *    - Securing service-to-service communication
 *    - Authentication/Authorization
 *    - API Gateway security
 * 
 * 6. INITIAL IMPLEMENTATION
 *    - More complex initial setup
 *    - Need for DevOps culture
 *    - Requires skilled team
 * 
 * ============================================================================
 * PART 4: HANDS-ON IMPLEMENTATION
 * ============================================================================
 */

